    Demo Party 01 - Person Requester on case 03 (In Progress General Inquiry)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the FIRST of the 8-party demo dataset; it pairs with
    sibling party 02 (Organization/Respondent on the same case 03) to
    demonstrate that the polymorphic UI Policy works correctly on
    General Inquiry case types - one Person row + one Organization row
    on the same case exercises BOTH conditional branches simultaneously.
    Together with parties 02 through 08, this record satisfies AAP
    Section 0.4.1's seed-data folder requirements for `seed-data/parties/`.

    The complete 8-party fixture matrix:

        Party 01 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)  ## THIS FILE
        Party 02 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Party 03 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Party 04 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 05 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 06 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 07 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 08 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)

    The 8-party dataset thus exercises:
      * All 2 `party_type` choice values (Person x5, Organization x3) -
        this party contributes the FIRST of the five Person entries;
        the Person branch demonstrates that the conditional UI Policy at
        ../../ui_policy/x_casemgmt_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
        correctly shows the <person> reference field and HIDES the
        <organization> reference field when party_type=Person. As the
        FIRST Person-branch row in the load sequence, this party is the
        canonical first invocation of the Person branch when a fresh
        PDI imports the Update Set; subsequent Person rows (parties 03,
        04, 06, and 08) reuse the same branch with different parent
        cases and distinct sys_user references.
      * All 3 example `role_label` values (Requester x3, Respondent x3,
        Witness x2) - this party contributes the FIRST of the three
        Requester entries (the others are party 04 on case 05 and
        party 06 on case 08). The Requester role semantically
        represents the entity who FILED the case - the requester of
        information, the complainant, or the primary point of contact
        on whose behalf the inquiry is being processed.
      * 5 unique parent cases (03, 04, 05, 08, 09) - this party is
        the FIRST party on case 03 (paired with party 02's Organization/
        Respondent); cases 03, 05, and 08 each have TWO parties
        (Person + Organization) demonstrating the dual-party pattern.
        Case 03 is the canonical In Progress General Inquiry exemplar;
        case 08 plays the analogous role for the Complaint flow.
      * Both flow paths (General Inquiry: cases 03, 04, 05 / Complaint:
        cases 08, 09) - this party tests the polymorphic Person branch
        on the GENERAL INQUIRY flow's In Progress case; party 06
        (Person Requester on case 08) tests the same on the Complaint
        flow's In Progress case. Together these two Person Requester
        rows on the same lifecycle phase (In Progress) but different
        flow paths prove the Person branch works on both flows.
      * All 3 demo users in the `person` slot (demo_manager x2, demo_agent
        x2, demo_viewer x1) - this party contributes the FIRST appearance
        of demo_manager in the Update Set load sequence; party 06 on
        case 08 (Person Requester / In Progress Complaint) is the SECOND
        appearance of demo_manager, demonstrating that the same internal
        user can be recorded as the Requester on multiple cases (a normal
        operational scenario where one manager intakes inquiries across
        multiple subject matters over time). The manager is also
        referenced in cases 01-10 as either assigned_agent or via
        sys_created_by audit fields, but those references are at the
        case level, not the party level.

    Lifecycle position - WHY Person / Requester / parent General Inquiry
    case In Progress is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.7 the case_party schema is:
          case        - Reference -> x_casemgmt_case (mandatory)
          party_type  - Choice (Person | Organization, mandatory)
          person      - Reference -> sys_user (conditional: required
                        if party_type=Person)
          organization- Reference -> core_company (conditional: required
                        if party_type=Organization)
          role_label  - String(100) (mandatory; example values
                        Requester, Respondent, Witness)

      With party_type=Person, the conditional UI Policy at
      ../../ui_policy/x_casemgmt_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
      activates the Person branch:
          - Show + require <person> field (populated below with
            "x_casemgmt_demo_manager")
          - Hide <organization> field (left empty below; the empty
            <organization/> element preserves the dictionary entry's
            existence while signaling no value)

      Case 03 is in In Progress status on the General Inquiry flow per
      ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_03.xml. The case was filed by an
      external requester submitting a General Inquiry; the demo team's
      queue accepted the inquiry, the manager assigned the demo agent,
      and the agent is now actively investigating. The
      <role_label>Requester</role_label> on this party records the demo
      manager as the REQUESTER OF RECORD - the entity who filed (or
      filed on behalf of someone for) the inquiry. This pattern parallels
      party 04 on case 05 (Resolved General Inquiry, Requester demo_viewer)
      and party 06 on case 08 (In Progress Complaint, Requester
      demo_agent); the same Requester role appearing on multiple cases
      with different demo users reflects the normal operational reality
      that any internal user can be the recorded Requester depending
      on who initiated the workflow.

      Note: the AAP Section 0.5.7 example role_label values are
      Requester, Respondent, Witness; this party uses Requester as the
      FIRST example of the Requester role in the load sequence,
      establishing the canonical Requester semantic that party 04
      and party 06 will replicate on subsequent cases.

