         branch pattern on a single case's Related List. This is the
         canonical UI Policy smoke test: on the case-03 form, the
         Related List shows BOTH parties; the polymorphic UI Policy
         renders this party with the person field visible (and the
         organization field hidden) and party 02 with the organization
         field visible (and the person field hidden) - simultaneously,
         on the same case, in the same Related List.
      2. THE display_value LOOKUPS ARE THE ACTUAL RESOLUTION MECHANISM.
         The inner element values (CASE0000003 for case, x_casemgmt_demo_
         manager for person, x_casemgmt for sys_scope/sys_package) are
         the HUMAN-READABLE LOOKUP KEYS that ServiceNow's Update Set
         engine resolves to the target records' sys_ids at import
         time. The display_value attribute is the canonical lookup
         key; the inner text mirrors it for clarity. NO hex-string
         sys_ids appear in any cross-reference field per AAP
         Section 0.7.2.
