         filed this request on behalf of someone or as the primary
         point of contact" - a typical scoped POC role. The canonical
         use-case: a manager intakes a verbal inquiry from an external
         party in the lobby, files the case on their behalf, and
         records themselves as the Requester until the external party
         is formally identified. This is one of three canonical
         Requester-role appearances in the 8-party fixture; the others
         (party 04 = demo_viewer on case 05, party 06 = demo_manager on
         case 08) demonstrate that the Requester can be any internal
         user depending on operational context - including the same
